title: Extensive Bilateral Pulmonary Embolism Secondary to Uterine Fibroid Induced Iliac Vein Compression; Case Report
content: This case represents the association between the presence of large fibroid tumor and pulmonary embolism in 47-year-old women. We highlight the diagnostic investigations and treatment methods for PE, followed by further evaluation of the underlying explanation of this pathology and eliminating other related risk factors.
